texts.text: >4 years ago.
Let's get married...
Huh? What's this all the sudden?
You know I don't have much longer.
I know. I'm serious.
Give me time to think it over...
Dr. Kayama! He's gone! He must've escaped!
What?! We need to find him!
>Dr. Kayama is hunched over beside the man's bed.
He had an event while in the alley next to the hospital...
He knew he shouldn't, but went outside anyways...
Why did he run...? He never gave me an answer either...
>Now.
>Your battle against Murmur continues.
Doctor... Pain...
I'm... Sorry...
>Dr. Kayama continues to babble as she's floats in the air.
Die... Everyone...

*Wince*
They're too strong.

*Pant*
We need... Backup...
Go my spirits.
Stop...!
No!
Here! Over here!
>The spirits set their sights on the boy.

*Groan*
This is rough, but now's your chance...!
It's now or never! Fire!
User every demon you have!
We have no choice!
*Roar*
*Roar*
*Groan*
>The spirits begin to disappear.
What... Where am I...?
Dr. Kayama! You're back!
Thank... You...
You were all my patients...? I'm so sorry.
You... Tried... Your best... Thank you...
You... Did... What you could... Thanks...

*Whimper*
Thank you... Thank you... Everyone...
No... My army of the dead... All gone...

*Pant*
I'm out of demons...

*Pant*
I'm down to my last one...
Newbie's in a tough spot too...
This is all we get against Murmur...
Then it is your turn to become my spirits!
*Wince*
We can do it! Let's go, Newbie!
That will not be necessary.
Gemori?!
Out of my way, Gemori!
You have lost. It is time for you to fall back.
Nay. I am far from being defeated.
If you perish here, then your fate will truly be sealed.
Bah... If only I were at my full strength...!
I have no choice. I yield...
Wait.
Please, at least grant my wish.
Such insolence.
I am still your summoner.
Ah, yes. My purpose is to grant my summoner's wishes.
You did somehow summon me into this realm, albeit in a flawed manner...
As a reward and as my last act, I shall grant thy wish.
Then...!
Fine. Spirit, hear my call...
Huh? Oh hey, it's been a while.
Now, ask him what you wish to ask.
Give me your answer. From that day.
Oh, you proposed to me. I guess that really did happen.
Don't play dumb. I'm still serious.
It didn't matter that our time together would be short as long as I was with you.
But you decided to run away
and left me all alone in the end.
No... It wasn't like that.
What the hell do you mean?!
Here. I never got a chance to give this to you.
>The man presents Dr. Kayama with a ring.
Is that an engagement ring?
Is this why you left the hospital? To buy this?!
Yep. But I ended up losing my life in return. Talk about irony.
You idiot! You didn't have to do that...!
I'm so sorry.
>Dr. Kayama accepts the ring but it immediately vanishes...
Anything belonging to the dead can't be brought back into the real world. Sorry.
No. It's fine. I'm...
But your new friends are all really young.
Huh?
>Dr. Kayama turns around and sees all the people showing worry for her.
Doctor...
Regardless of me giving you that ring,
you should try to find happiness with your friends that are actually alive.
I think that's what I really wanted to say.
Will you hear me out?
Fine... You're not here anymore,
and this world felt empty and meaningless once you were gone.
But if you really think so... I'll try to find happiness in some other way...!
Haha. You're gonna be just fine.
>The man slowly begins to fade away.
I guess I'm out of time. I'm glad I got to see you again.
>He disappears...
He's gone...
Ah...! Aaahhhhhhhh!
It seems you have settled back down...
To my chagrin, I will admit defeat and bide my time until my next chance arrives.
I vow to raise an army and create a world utterly saturated with chaos...
And you. Gemori. You saw this future, did you now?
Yes. You ran amok by yourself and still lost to these young ones.
You are one "his" most prized pieces... The time to battle "them" is close...
We cannot afford to lose you. Do so at least for "him"...
And I still have preparations to make in this world...
Ha. You never change...
Gemori...?
>Yu senses a kind of fear for Gemori he didn't until now.
Yu? Is something the matter?
Uh, no... It's nothing...
I have a feeling we have not seen the last of you, humans...
>Murmur disappears without saying anything further...
It's finally over. Any more and that might've been it for us.
Yu, everyone... I'm so sorry for everything that happened...
No! We're glad you're safe!
And Gemori... Thanks for helping us in the end.
Mind you it was not for you sake...
But you still have a wish, yes?
With my powers, this doctor will be eating out of the palm of your hand.
She will be your lover in every way and you need not feel any remorse.
Me?!
That was my plan initially.
But after being saved by you, Gemori... Now, I think...
Now? Tell me?
I think I've fallen in love with you, Gemori!!
Oh...
Wow.
You're pretty and mysterious and never jealous of anyone...
My heart won't stop pounding. I've never felt this way about anyone before.
Gemori, please go out with me!
Wait... Doesn't that mean Gemori knew this would happen too?
No, I had no way of foreseeing anything like this from happening.
An unresolved part of the future was changed somehow.
Gemori, you'll grant me my wish, right?
You must know that I cannot...
Hey, what are you doing down here?!
We're busted.
Oh, I'm sorry! We were just leaving!
I should get back to work now that I feel much better.
And let me pay you all back for causing all of this trouble.
You can all come back and visit whenever you like too.
There she goes.
Gemori...!
Now, what am I to do? Do you devil users have any solutions?
I mean... We're not the ones being confessed to so...
Right. You need to present your true feeling to him.
I see. But woe is me.
To think that the courier of a woman's love would be subject to something like this.

*Chuckle*
C'est la vie.
